Two miners died and a further 10 are
missing after being buried alive at a gold mine in northwestern
Tanzania, the  Daily News  reported, citing police officials it
didnâ€™t identify.  The miners were working at a mine in Geita, about 1,000
kilometers (622 miles) northwest of Dar es Salaam, the
commercial capital, the newspaper said. The gold mine is owned
by a resident of Nyarugusu village, it said.  Police have banned mining in the area and security has been
stepped up to try and stop illegal mining, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
